

==================================> Superblock recovery in 7.6 <==================================

  #df -h /data
  
  #umount /data 
  
  #dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/vg1/lv1 bs=1M count=10  ============> To destroy superblock

  #xfs_repair -L /dev/vg1/lv1 =============> If u dont use 'L' , ur data will be lost so use 'L'.
  
  #mount /dev/vg1/lv1 /data
  
 =======> No need to recover superblock from backup superblock ( mke2fs -n <bkp superblock id> <device name ) like in rhel 6.9
  
================================================================================================================================


==================================> To See Superblock info in 7.6 <==================================

  #df -h /data
  
  #umount /data/ 
  
  #xfs_db /dev/vg1/lv1
  
   xfs_db> sb  (superblock)
   xfs_db> p  ===========> To display details such as the magic number, Inode info, UUID, block size, data blocks count, and more.
   xfs_db> q    (To Quit)
   
  #mount /dev/vg1/lv1 /data
  
  #cd /data/  ===========> Data will be available.
 
